text.tspan: 1. Connect the SStM32L0G1C Logic Analyzer to your computer using a USB-C
cable. A USB Serial/COM port should appear (typically in /dev/ on Linux
2. Launch PulseView and open the device selection menu.
3. Choose Openbench Logic Sniffer & SUMP compatibles (ols) and choose the
Your Logic Analyzer is now connected to your computer.
Important notes when using the Logic Analyzer:
* Never connect probes while the Device under Test is powered.
* GND pins should be unnecessary if the Logic Analyzer and Device under Test
is connected to the same computer. Please consult an organizer before
connecting a GND probe to avoid risks of electrical shorts.
